description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for highly motivated nurse to use their existing skills and knowledge to provide high quality care for our valuable workforce, and external customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be an experienced registered nurse, with a genuine interest in Occupational Health with excellent interpersonal skills and first rate client and customer service talents. You should be able to work autonomously, and flexibly as part of an experienced and enthusiastic multi-disciplinary team. You should be able to use computerised patient record systems, and Microsoft office.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties will include; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrying out pre employment health checks and advising on adjustments required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Making individual health needs assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assisting in the audit process of the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Offering support and signposting to counsellor, or physiotherapist etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assessing and managing workplace risks, carrying out Display screen assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carrying out surveillance testing such as Audiometry, Spirometry, Skin and HAV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vaccinations, such as the flu jab, hepatitis B etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Taking blood samples&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Advising on Needle stick injuries and following high risk incidents up&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Involvement in follow up of Infection Control outbreaks in the hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Previous experience of using Cohort Occupational Health software or similar would be an advantage although full training will be given. We operate a paperless office maximising the use of electronic technology which helps us to achieve responsive turnaround times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be based in our purpose built premises in Worcester, and will involve travelling across Worcestershire and adjoining counties to provide Occupational Health advice to our NHS, public and private sector clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time and part time working options will be considered&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please email Felicity Davies, Deputy Director of People &amp; Culture on f.davies2@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
